Eskom is set to conduct an internal investigation after a body of a woman was recovered in her office on Monday.Thembisile Yende,30, an Eskom employee went missing almost two weeks ago.Eskom&#8217;s Khulu Phasiwe says as the company they will conduct an internal investigation to trace what happened.&#8220;There are cameras showing Yende coming in when she arrived at work but after that there is nothing showing on camera as they went black.&#8221;It is reported that Yende&#8217;s relatives opened a missing person&#8217;s case, they learnt that her work car was parked at the substation.Meanwhile the family of the deceased has lambasted Eskom for handling the case.Family spokesperson Mboneni Yende said Eskom killed her sister.TNA Reporter 